# GENERATED VIEW (#1640 S13, PARTIAL/SCOPED — M1 close). The six CC_ROLE_<ROLE>_MODEL= tier-pin lines below
# are a generated view of the router SSOT (config/cc-routes.json): each is seats.<role>.model resolved
# through providers.<id>.model_vocabulary[...].tier_equivalent. Do NOT hand-edit those six lines directly —
# edit config/cc-routes.json's seats instead, then re-render / re-verify with
# `scripts/render-route-views.sh --check-roles-env config/cc-roles.env` (the drift sentinel; nonzero + names
# the divergent CC_ROLE_*_MODEL key on mismatch). Every OTHER line in this file — EFFORT, the MODEL-VERSION
# pin table, and all prose/rationale below — is HAND-AUTHORED and intentionally OUT of the generated view's
# scope: the router SSOT schema has no effort or version field yet (a genuine, disclosed scope limit; see the
# #1640 plan's advisory A2 / `## Deferred-follow-ups`), so those levers stay operator-set policy in this file.
# This is a SCOPED generated view (six lines), not a full-file codegen — see #1640 S5 (scripts/render-route-
# views.sh) for the M0 preview generator this view is now the live target of.
#
# PORT-NOTE (#1448): per-role model policy for the interactive 4-role chain, distributed via the three-role-model
#   plugin so every consuming repo inherits Option A (Opus on planner + both review gates, Sonnet on the executor).
#   Generated byte-identical from ai-brain canonical config/cc-roles.env by scripts/sync-three-role-plugin.mjs;
#   never hand-edit. In the plugin the ledger helper lives at bin/3role-ledger.mjs (the comment below names it
#   hooks/3role-ledger.mjs in ai-brain-canonical form — comment-only, nothing reads the config's comments).
# Per-role model+effort policy for the INTERACTIVE 4-role chain (#1448).
# Extended with a per-tier MODEL-VERSION pin table (#1458) — see the enforcement matrix below.
#
# Namespaced CC_ROLE_* to avoid collision with cc-models.env (the Ollama cron/benchmark pipeline's bare
# PLANNER_MODEL / EXECUTOR_MODEL, which name Qwen tags — a DIFFERENT model universe; keep the files separate).
#
#   model   in {opus, sonnet, haiku, fable}      (the Agent/Task `model:` tier)
#   effort  in {low, medium, high, xhigh}        (reasoning effort)
#   version = a concrete claude-* model id       (the tier's blessed EXACT edition — see the pin table below)
#
# ── PER-LEVER ENFORCEMENT MATRIX (#1458 — honest split: every lever states what is a hard wall vs a note) ───
#   | Lever         | Enforced how                                                    | Surface                     |
#   |---------------|------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------|
#   | MODEL TIER    | MECHANICALLY — transcript message.model -> modelIdToTier ->     | completion gate (hard block)|
#   |               | compare to CC_ROLE_<ROLE>_MODEL. Fail-safe to opus.              | + leading-edge advisory     |
#   | MODEL VERSION | MECHANICALLY — transcript message.model == the pinned claude-*  | completion gate ONLY (the   |
#   |               | id (assert-latest / fail-on-drift). Fail-CLOSED on can't-tell   | spawn tool sees a tier      |
#   |               | ONLY when a pin is configured; DORMANT (no check at all) when   | ALIAS, never a concrete     |
#   |               | no pin is set for that tier/role.                                | version, at spawn time)     |
#   | EFFORT        | REAL per-role (#1466): a dedicated agents/cc-<role>.md agent-    | agent-def effort:            |
#   |               | definition's effort: frontmatter overrides the inherited SESSION | frontmatter (the mechanism) |
#   |               | effort -- the override lives in the DEFINITION, not a spawn-tool  | + ledger effort field       |
#   |               | param (there still isn't one). OBSERVABLE: the ledger effort      | (assigned at SPAWN,          |
#   |               | field is sourced from the SubagentStop hook's effort.level (the   | observed at CLOSE via       |
#   |               | harness's OWN signal -- NOT the transcript, which never carries    | SubagentStop effort.level   |
#   |               | it); the OBSERVED value overwrites the ASSIGNED one on conflict.  | -- observed wins)           |
#   |               | No BLOCKING gate enforces it yet (a completion-time hard gate is  |                              |
#   |               | a clean follow-up, out of scope here) -- real + observed, not yet  |                              |
#   |               | mechanically enforced. CONSUMER NOTE: this config ships the       |                              |
#   |               | POLICY + the observability channel to every plugin consumer;      |                              |
#   |               | REALIZING the mechanism needs the consumer's OWN agents/cc-<role>  |                              |
#   |               | .md definitions (ai-brain-local this ticket, not ported here).    |                              |
#
# FAIL-SAFE (MODEL TIER): a missing/malformed file OR a missing/invalid per-role *_MODEL key => that role
# falls back to OPUS (today's all-Opus behavior). NEVER fail-open-to-cheap — a typo must cost quality-safe
# Opus, not silently a weaker tier. `node hooks/3role-ledger.mjs resolve-role-model --role <role>` reads this
# file (fail-safe to opus) and is the single command the orchestrator + both model hooks consume.
#
# OPTION A (cost-aware mix, operator-chosen 2026-07-03): Opus on the seats where a mistake is expensive
# (orchestrator + planner + BOTH review gates); Sonnet on the highest-volume grunt seats (executor + the
# NEW research seat). This stretches the monthly usage bar without weakening any quality gate. See the plans
# `.ai-workspace/plans/2026-07-03-1448-per-role-model-policy.md` and
# `.ai-workspace/plans/2026-07-03-1458-per-role-control-surface.md`.

# Orchestrator = the always-on MAIN session (not a spawned subagent). Policy/lint entry only — NOT
# transcript-enforced (there is no per-orchestrator subagent transcript to read). NEVER pin to fable (the
# config lint refuses it: a 2x-Opus always-on seat burns the Fable bar). Effort stays xhigh (#1458,
# operator decision 2026-07-03: the orchestrator "thinks harder").
#
# MOVED OPUS -> SONNET 5 on 2026-07-20 (operator decision, #1749), same measurement as the planner block
# below: the ALL-MODELS weekly bar read 74% used on day 2 of a 7-day window. The planner flip alone cannot
# touch that bar -- moving the planner off Fable converts Fable tokens into Opus tokens, which still count
# against all-models. The orchestrator is the only seat large enough to move it: it is the always-on seat
# carrying the full standing context, and the 28-day census measured it cache-read dominated. Two bars, two
# levers, neither substitutes for the other.
#
# THIS LINE IS A POLICY RECORD, NOT THE SWITCH. Because the orchestrator is the main session and not a
# spawned subagent, nothing here changes what the session actually runs -- the operator performs the live
# switch with `/model` in the session. So this key CAN legitimately disagree with reality for a while, and
# because the entry is not transcript-enforced no gate will catch the drift. If you are auditing, read the
# session's own model, never this line.
#
# STAYS ANTHROPIC. Do NOT route this seat through a non-Anthropic gateway: it holds the operator's full
# private standing context, which is the whole basis of the #1738 ruling, and the standing routing policy
# sends only NON-Anthropic models through the gateway (Sonnet 5 is Anthropic, so it goes direct via Max).
CC_ROLE_ORCHESTRATOR_MODEL=sonnet
CC_ROLE_ORCHESTRATOR_EFFORT=xhigh

# Planner — OPUS. Moved off Fable 2026-07-20 (operator decision, #1749) because THE CAP BOUND.
#
# WHAT CHANGED, and it is a measurement, not a re-argument. The prior standing-Fable rationale (operator
# directive 2026-07-17/18 under #1638, corrected + made durable 2026-07-19 under #1679) was CORRECT and is
# NOT being called a mistake: Fable-5 carries no expiry -- it is a permanent part of the Max/Team-Premium
# plans, capped at 50% of the weekly limit -- and the real constraint was always that weekly cap rather than
# a deadline. The seat was deliberately placed on Fable because the planner is the highest-leverage seat
# (design + hard research), i.e. the seat worth spending the cap on. On 2026-07-20 the usage panel read
# **Fable weekly 87% used on day 2 of a 7-day window** (all-models 74% the same day). The cap that seat was
# designed to spend was spent, with ~4.5 days left to run. The seat policy was sound; the burn rate was not
# anticipated.
#
# THIS IS THE #1574 HARD TRIGGER FIRING, NOT A REVERSAL OF #1679. #1574 records the revert condition
# "after 12 July OR at Fable quota exhaustion". The date half was voided with the false cost-cliff premise;
# the QUOTA-EXHAUSTION half was never voided and has now fired on measured data. (The superseded text here
# claimed "there is no revert trigger left to fire" -- that sentence was true only of the date trigger and
# is corrected by this edit. Do not restore it.)
#
# THE HISTORIC ~2x-Opus-per-token FIGURE still applies to API/usage-credit billing ONLY; it does not
# describe Max-plan-included usage. It is not the reason for this move -- the weekly cap is.
#
# DO NOT REVERT ON THE LEVERAGE ARGUMENT ALONE. Restoring Fable here needs a budget model that survives a
# full 7-day week, measured after a reset -- not a restatement of "the planner is the highest-leverage seat"
# (which remains true and was never in dispute). #1662 (weekly burn-down meter) is the instrument that would
# have caught this before the cap bound; #1571 still records that the planner=Fable bet was never settled by
# measurement. Effort stays xhigh.
CC_ROLE_PLANNER_MODEL=opus
CC_ROLE_PLANNER_EFFORT=xhigh

# Plan-review — UNCHANGED by #1569 (the #1506 bake-off returned NO-GO for this seat too, quality_gate=fail,
# and the operator did not override it here). Stays Opus. Effort high -> xhigh (#1496, operator-approved table
# 2026-07-09): raised alongside execution-review so BOTH review gates run at the highest effort.
CC_ROLE_PLAN_REVIEW_MODEL=opus
CC_ROLE_PLAN_REVIEW_EFFORT=xhigh

# Executor — the highest-volume seat (types the most); Sonnet is plenty-capable and much cheaper. This is the
# one seat Option A moves DOWN from Opus. Effort high -> medium (#1466, operator decision 2026-07-04): now that
# effort is REAL per-role (a dedicated agent-definition, not just a policy row), the executor is the seat where
# the cost-down mix makes most sense -- medium suffices for briefed mechanical work on the highest-volume seat.
# Effort medium -> high (#1496, operator-approved table 2026-07-09): switching the mechanism ON (the
# agents/cc-*.md definitions are now installed as live symlinks, per #1466) meant the OLD medium value would
# have been a live downgrade from the xhigh the seat inherits today -- raising it to the approved table value
# removes that downgrade. Operator-tunable: one config line; bump back down if NEEDS-WORK loops rise.
#   Cost-down alt (opt-in, NOT a default): CC_ROLE_EXECUTOR_MODEL=haiku for trivial-mechanical work only —
#   raises NEEDS-WORK loops on anything non-trivial, so set it per-run, never standing.
CC_ROLE_EXECUTOR_MODEL=sonnet
CC_ROLE_EXECUTOR_EFFORT=high

# Execution-review — Opus (#1574, operator directive 2026-07-16), effort high -> xhigh. The #1569 Fable
# adoption (opus -> fable @high, 2026-07-11) WAS the #1506 bake-off's measured GO (5/6 task wins, quality_delta
# +0.88, at 53% of output tokens, handicapped Fable@high vs Opus@xhigh) -- a real result, kept on file. It was
# rolled back on a since-voided cost claim (#1679, 2026-07-19: Fable-5 carries no expiry -- see the "Planner"
# comment above for the full correction). Execution-review stays Opus regardless, as the never-self-review
# gate's highest-scrutiny seat -- a deliberate seat choice, not a cost workaround. Re-adopt Fable via the
# opt-in path (below) if the operator flags execution-review as a Fable special-task seat.
CC_ROLE_EXECUTION_REVIEW_MODEL=opus
CC_ROLE_EXECUTION_REVIEW_EFFORT=xhigh

# Research/search seat (NEW, #1458) — the ad-hoc Explore/research subagents the orchestrator spawns for
# lookups. Sonnet is plenty-capable for a search/summarize seat at a fraction of Opus cost. NOT one of the
# four transcript-enforced REQUIRED_ROLES (planner/plan-review/executor/execution-review) — this seat is
# resolvable via `resolve-role-model --role research` (the orchestrator passes model:sonnet at spawn time) but
# is never gate-blocked at completion time (it is not a REQUIRED_ROLE). Effort high -> medium (#1466): a
# search/summarize seat doesn't need high effort either. Effort medium -> high (#1496, operator-approved table
# 2026-07-09): same live-downgrade-removal rationale as the executor above. DEFERRED (out of scope for #1458):
# wiring this seat into a completion-time gate — it is still not a REQUIRED_ROLE and never blocks a close.
# #1516: research spawns NOW carry 3ROLE_TASK:<id> ROLE:research as doctrine (parent-claude.md Invariant #6,
# agents/cc-research.md) — the spawn-time ledger row (hooks/three-role-spawn-ledger.sh, PreToolUse edge,
# research-only) is what makes this seat visible on the live board WHILE it runs, not just at close.
CC_ROLE_RESEARCH_MODEL=sonnet
CC_ROLE_RESEARCH_EFFORT=high

# Fable seats — THERE ARE NONE as of 2026-07-20 (#1749). The planner was the last standing Fable seat and
# moved to Opus when the weekly cap bound at 87% on day 2 of 7 (see the Planner block above for the full
# measurement and why this is the #1574 quota trigger firing, not a reversal of #1679). Execution-review
# stays Opus by deliberate choice, not cost.
#
# STILL TRUE, and the reason a future Fable pin is not forbidden: #1679 (2026-07-19) corrected the standing
# rationale for good -- Fable-5 carries no expiry (a permanent part of the Max/Team-Premium plans, capped at
# 50% of the weekly limit). The real constraint is that weekly cap, not a deadline. So the rule for any
# future pin is unchanged: keep it on the highest-leverage seat (design, hard research), never a high-volume
# grunt seat -- AND size it against a burn model that survives a full 7-day week, which is the half this
# repo did not have and #1662 (weekly burn-down meter) exists to supply.
#
# Because no seat reads fable today, the config lint's FABLE-CAP-BUDGET note (emitted on any *_MODEL=fable
# read, by design) no longer fires from this file. That silence is EXPECTED and is not evidence the lint
# broke -- re-pin any seat to fable and it returns. The historic ~2x-Opus-per-token figure still applies to
# API/usage-credit billing only, never to Max-plan-included usage. #1497 (three-key opt-in Fable gate)
# tracks a structured opt-in path for any seat that wants a per-run Fable pin; #1571 records that the
# planner=Fable bet was never settled by measurement, which is still open.

# ── MODEL-VERSION pins (#1458 — assert-latest / fail-on-drift) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# A tier alias ("sonnet") resolves to the tier's LATEST concrete version, revealed only in the transcript
# message.model. Pin the exact latest we last blessed; the completion gate FAILS LOUDLY if a role's
# transcript model != the pin (the platform silently bumped the latest, OR a role ran on an unexpected
# version) so a human updates the pin DELIBERATELY. Update path = edit here, then re-run the plugin sync.
# A tier with NO pin here leaves the version sub-leg DORMANT for every role at that tier (the tier leg alone
# still enforces) — deliberate, not a gap: it lets a consumer adopt tier enforcement (#1448) without opting
# into version drift-detection (#1458) until it is ready to bless a first pin.
CC_TIER_OPUS_VERSION=claude-opus-4-8
CC_TIER_SONNET_VERSION=claude-sonnet-5
CC_TIER_HAIKU_VERSION=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
CC_TIER_FABLE_VERSION=claude-fable-5
# Optional per-ROLE override (default UNSET): assert one role must run an exact version, overriding the
# per-tier pin for that role's expected tier. Rarely needed (the spawn alias can't select an OLD version) —
# this is an ASSERTION knob (validate one seat mid-migration), never a SELECTION knob.
#   CC_ROLE_EXECUTOR_MODEL_VERSION=claude-sonnet-5
